result.name: Hill Wood Hot Pot

reviews.text: One of the best hot pot you could get. Just have to know what to order though because there is so much variety you could choose from.
Simply authentic Hong Kong style hot pot for beef and seafood, don't miss it's hand made dumplings as staple food towards the end of dinner.

This is a really local hot pot joint in this restaurant street on the Kowloon side, in the Tsimshatsui area.
Really local means the interior decorations are basic, and the chefs and staff sits outside when things are going slower, and chat with the regulars. 
The sliced local beef here is excellent. The Chinese people haven't discovered aging and hanging beef, and prefer them fresh. The belief is once ingredients have been frozen their taste and texture are compromised. The tenderness of the beef comes entirely from the selection of marbled cuts. The beef taste is prominent.
In addition, they have good seafood for the hotpot. We really enjoyed razor clams from Scotland.
The price is fair. I don't think you are made to pay for interior decorations, which they had none.
I am told that one can find equivalent hotpot places in less touristy areas of Kowloon, at lower prices. Frankly, this one is good enough for me and I am not interested in searching out those other ones in areas where parking is a problem and one has to learn how to navigate various unfamiliar streets. 
I have been back several times and enjoyed my meals every time.
food is nice and service is good

Excellent hot pot shop. Everything is fresh. Certainly, if you consume fresh seafood, your bill will be bigger.

Elephant trunk clam, abalone, large clam, tender beef,  +3000is a must. But, worth it.
